snippet.title: Definitely The Actions Of A "Victim".
snippet.description:
Since Discovery+ has done a documentary on Johnny Depp and Amber Heard and have left out all the evidence that she abused him,i thought it poignant to re find this clip. Discovery+ has spun the narrative that she was a victim, discovery is owned by Warner bros so have a financial insentive to make Amber look good because of Aquaman 2 and how many people have said they would boycott it, and you have morons eating it up because of selective narrative portrayal.

Since they've advertised this, i decided to ask a question of the people saying she was a victim 

"To anyone saying he abused her, just answer a simple question for me: what abuse victim do you know is actively caught on audio MOCKING their abuser and admitting to hitting them, then daring them to go public about how you hit them because "no one will believe that you're a victim of domestic violence because I'm just a dainty girl and you're a big strong man". Does that sound like the language of an abused person in your minds? If it does then you need to seek psychological help because you're as narcissistic as she is.". 

Let me know in the Comments if this is the attitude of a" victim" in your opinions.
